{"id": "1435659185554587668", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "author_id": "264894122148495362", "author_name": "sirtealot", "content": "While it doesn't matter much in the early game, Daffodil and Liz don't really fit into the same team\n-# Unless you're using Daff as a support, but that is a bit of a waste of her potential <:Calm:1400771586545553408> \n\nDaff wants to be paired with characters that stack strength for her and to land most of the killing blows herself for scaling\nAnd Liz kinda just does her own thing with poison burst turns\n\nI'd suggest replacing Liz with Ogier at first and either Casiah or Clementine later on", "timestamp": "2025-11-05T15:57:03.094000+00:00", "type": 19, "mentions": ["653067823836430346"], "reply_to": "1435606646159310849"}
{"id": "1435660295111573634", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "author_id": "264894122148495362", "author_name": "sirtealot", "content": "Winkle is an aliemus battery support with unique utility on her E3, allowing you to use other character's exalt twice in a single turn\nAnd a consistent source of weakness too\n\nAll those things will become a lot more relevant later into the game, so you'll start appreciating her more", "timestamp": "2025-11-05T16:01:27.633000+00:00", "type": 19, "mentions": ["653067823836430346"], "reply_to": "1435607203674456235"}
